  "elapsed_s": 101.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So we arrive to this moment, in which [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was born my new sister.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was born in 1945, the 10th of December.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] At the time, I already [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was very intensively playing my violin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And what I remember was that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] time to time, when I was playing the violin, I was seeing [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] my mother [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] crying.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And during this time-- how I mentioned my father was mostly outside of the city, traveling to provide the money for survival.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was working at home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the climate, the, the atmosphere was very-- basically, very depressed, depressed situation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I started to go in regular school, started my studies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] immediately, something-- what happened kind of, for a little while, refreshed the climate inside of my house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was that I was accepted as a youngest member-- or from that time-- for children orchestra in the capital.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [SIGHS] Not only that, but I very soon become not only the concertmaster there, but also the soloist of this orchestra.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was one side of my life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The same time were happening the other thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Soon as my new sister was born, my--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She-- her name was-- she was given the name [NON-ENGLISH] Margareta.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was-- my mother became very badly depressed, very, very sick.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was-- I was seeing her all the time in one very badly crying mood.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
